					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/oboebandgeek99" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1782920); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1782920&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252513" alt="Oboebandgeek99" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1782920)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/oboebandgeek99" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1782920); return false;" >Oboebandgeek99</a></span> <span class="odate time_1568683814 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 Sep 2019 01:30</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4366258">
									

<p>I'm really glad you like it and took the time to tell me so! I left the alien species vague for many reasons so it's really up to the reader to decide what species the aliens are or what they look like. The tale in many ways is somewhat allegorical to historical and even present-day (ugh) discrimination against couples (interracial, lgbt, etc), but it's hard to say if they're a gay or queer couple because in my mind alien gender doesn't really map onto the human gender binary, and maybe how sexuality is typically spoken about would be completely different (but for the record, Rion would probably identify as pansexual).</p>
<p>And you should totally write about space love too, take it from me, it's a lot of fun!</p>

							</div>

								
					
