														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4852168">
									

<p>I really liked the fact that it wasn't clear. This forced the reader to concentrate on the characters and plot. The beauty of SCI-FI is that you can address these issues by changing the situation without changing the question. (Eeh, it sounds so two-dimensional, but I hope you understand what I mean.) Also the point that our culture and the way we treat our bodies does not automatically apply to other life forms is very real and makes it more interesting to see how we interact. This reminds me of &quot;The Long Way to a Small, Angry Planet&quot;, a fantastic book that I only recommend to you.</p>
<p>I'm sorry I'm so late replying, but I swore I wouldn't write a reply until my story was finished, which <a href="http://scp-wiki-de.wikidot.com/das-taegliche-leben-mit-einer-ausserirdischen">it is now</a> after more than a year! I'll try to translate it and put it in <a href="http://scp-int.wikidot.com/das-taegliche-leben-mit-einer-ausserirdischen">INT</a> and maybe <a class="newpage" href="/das-taegliche-leben-mit-einer-ausserirdischen">EN</a>.</p>

