		<div class="post" id="post-4817935">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4817935)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4817935">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jakelope13" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4535677); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4535677&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252513" alt="Jakelope13" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4535677)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jakelope13" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4535677); return false;" >Jakelope13</a></span> <span class="odate time_1605310898 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Nov 2020 23:41</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4817935">
									

<p>Really enjoyed the story, especially the presentation of&#8230;. confusion? which would surround either the first, or one of the first, inter-species romantic relationship. While I'm not a fan of how the Foundation are presented, it's entirely believable. After all, all the Martian Ethics Committee head wanted to do was prevent a potential diplomatic incident. And she succeeded in doing so, by creating a different (and much, much thornier) diplomatic incident.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;One&nbsp;question,&nbsp;though</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;This&nbsp;is&nbsp;my&nbsp;headcanon,&nbsp;but&nbsp;wanted&nbsp;to&nbsp;know&nbsp;if&nbsp;it&nbsp;was&nbsp;the&nbsp;author's&nbsp;intent</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Was Valentina acting on her own? It felt like she was attempting to head off what she though would be a potential nightmare, but in reality was completely overstepping her authority in not conferring with the rest of the Ethics Committee on this matter. Part of what was reinforcing the idea was what the Foundation Agent said to Orion. After all, you'd think even the average agent would be at least smart enough to <em>not</em> speak like that to someone who would become the center of social attention in the extremely near future.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Firm +1 from me.</p>

							</div>

								
					
