				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/oboebandgeek99" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1782920); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1782920&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252513" alt="Oboebandgeek99" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1782920)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/oboebandgeek99" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1782920); return false;" >Oboebandgeek99</a></span> <span class="odate time_1607655081 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Dec 2020 02:51</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4841918">
									

<p>Yeah, the Foundation tends to be a bit darker/less ethical in aapa overall, so i decided to play with that a bit.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;with&nbsp;regards&nbsp;to&nbsp;your&nbsp;headcanon...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;hmm.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>You're getting close to what I intended. I didn't discuss this with nat bc I wasn't sure if I'd revisit these characters, but I have some opinions on what the deal is with Valentina.</p>
<p>Isn't it kind of weird how they never saw any other members of the ethics committee? Even the voice that called the parents into her office was specifically described as being inhuman.</p>
<p>What a weird detail to point in a collapsible for no reason.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Thanks for the upvote and thoughtful commentary!</p>

							</div>

								
					
